Defendant in custody on WRIT.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of five and one-half (5.5) years. That is two and one-half (2.5) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, concurrent with the sentence imposed on 16 CF 194 and concurrent with the sentences presently being served on Sheboygan County case no: 15 CF 392 and 15 CF 324.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) maintain fulltime employment or work search;
4) maintain absolute sobriety;
5) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
6) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
7) Any counseling deemed appropriate by the agent;
8) No contact with any known drug dealers or users.
Minutes.
